definition.value: A member of the class of  pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole substituted by a methyl group at position 4.
A macrocycle composed of 4,6-dihydroxy-1,3-phenylene groups linked by methylene groups. The number of 4,6-dihydroxy-1,3-phenylene units in the macrocycle is denoted by the "n" in calixresorc[n]arene.
Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having two free valences at carbon atom(s).

A macrocycle consisting of repeating  2,5-dioxodihydroimidazo[4,5-d]imidazole-1,3,4,6-tetrayl (glycoluril) units linked by methylene groups. The number of glycoluril units in the macrocycle is denoted by the "n" in cucurbit[n]uril name.
A hormone antagonist that blocks endothelin receptors.
A endothelin receptor antagonist is a drug which selectively blocks endothelin A receptors.
A carnitinium that is the conjugate acid of (S)-carnitine.
Cyclopropane and its derivatives formed by substitution.
A carbocyclic compound that is cyclopropene and its derivatives formed by substitution.
